quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  29,7,"As for those who believe and do good, We will certainly absolve them of their sins, and reward them according to the best of what they used to do"
  29,8,"We have commanded people to honour their parents. But if they urge you to associate with Me what you have no knowledge of, then do not obey them. To Me you will ˹all˺ return, and then I will inform you of what you used to do"
  29,9,Those who believe and do good will surely be admitted by Us into ˹the company of˺ the righteous
  29,10,"There are some who say, “We believe in God,” but when they suffer in the cause of God, they mistake ˹this˺ persecution at the hands of people for the punishment of God. But when victory comes from your Lord, they surely say ˹to the believers˺, “We have always been with you.” Does God not know best what is in the hearts of all beings"
  29,11,God will certainly distinguish between those who have ˹sure˺ faith and the hypocrites
  29,12,"The disbelievers say to the believers, “˹Just˺ follow our way, and we will bear ˹the burden of˺ your sins.” But they would never ˹want to˺ bear any of the believers’ sins. They are simply lying"
  29,13,"Yet they will certainly ˹be made to˺ carry their own burdens, as well as other burdens along with their own. And they will surely be questioned on Judgment Day about what they used to fabricate"
  29,14,"Indeed, We sent Noah to his people, and he remained among them for a thousand years, less fifty. Then the Flood overtook them, while they persisted in wrongdoing"